import math
for i in range(int(input())):
    N = list(map(int, input().split()))
    a = N[0]
    b = N[1]
    P = ''
    if b < 9:
        P = P + str(1) + ' '
        P = P + str(math.ceil(b / 9))
    elif a > b:
        P = P + str(1) + ' '
        P = P + str(math.ceil(b / 9))
    else:
        P = P + str(0) + ' '
        P = P + str(math.ceil(a / 9))
    print(P)

import math
for i in range(int(input())):
    (a, b) = map(int, input().split())
    r1 = math.ceil(a / 9)
    r2 = math.ceil(b / 9)
    if r1 >= r2:
        print('1', end=' ')
        print(r2)
    else:
        print('0', end=' ')
        print(r1)
